  "text": "Immunoblotting was performed as described in our previous reports. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In brief, cells were lysed and the total proteins were quantified using the Bradford assay (Bio-Rad, 500-0006). Equal amounts of total protein (25 mg) in each sample were loaded onto a 15% SDS-PAGE gel. After transferring, the blot was incubated with a rabbit anti-LC3B (1:1000), a rabbit anti-MTOR (1:1000), a rabbit anti-phospho-MTOR (1:1000), a mouse anti-SQSTM1/p62 (1:200), or a mouse HRP-conjugated anti-actin (1:30000) antibody. Images were taken using a ChemiDoc TM MP System (BioRad, Hercules, CA). The intensity of the band was quantified using Image Lab software (Bio-Rad) or ImageJ as described earlier. The fold change of LC3B-II is defined as the ratio of the intensity of the LC3B-II band normalized to that of actin.",
